x221.png 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-800x596.png 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-120x89.png 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-768x572.png 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-1536x1144.png 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-2048x1525.png 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-485x360.png 485w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-696x518.png 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-1068x795.png 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-1920x1430.png 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-564x420.png 564w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-80x60.png 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/Screen-Shot-2020-12-03-at-1.45.58-PM-265x198.png 265w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-248210\">Speeco ABB give riders a UCI compliant option for getting as aero as [legally] possible. Photo c Speeco</figcaption></figure><p>Personally, I suspect (and secretly hope) that this ban pushes cycling industry engineers and designers to look at new ways to give the rider an aero advantage while toeing the UCI rulebook line – we’ve seen this happening already with products like the Speeco ABB featured here on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/12/03/speeco-abb-carbon-bar-stem-breaks-the-drop-bar-mold-in-search-of-aero-gains/\">BikeRumor</a> last December.</p><p>It is certainly a challenge to balance regulations that keep riders safe and those that keep the playing field level, but any way you slice it the UCI’s ban on the supertuck and TT positions reduce the number of tools that teams have to employ in race tactics. Whether or not that’s a good thing is up to you – let us know your thoughts in the comments!</p></div></div>","author":"Chris Chou","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2970c5048e8a0d8e3f8337c7e9ab06841677ba92992340d192333138ff32622a","category":"Cycling"}